race.description: Gowings Toyota Country Boosted Maiden Plate
race.comment: RAINBOW BLESSING (12) continued her good form this prep when she changed tactics and led last start before battling on gamely for second over 1350m at the Beaumont track. Rock hard fit and draws a nice gate. Looks the one to beat in a maiden that lacks a bit of depth. VENDOR (7) has settled in the second half of the field then worked home fairly in his two runs this prep, the latest over 1500m at Muswellbrook. Might sharpen up with the blinkers reapplied so give him one more chance. IRISH ACCOLADE (2) had a five-week let-up and a change of stables before his respectable fifth over the mile at Newcastle recently. In a far easier maiden today so should be in the finish. MEGANHEW (9) took on the new role of leader last start but wilted at the end of 1500m at Muswellbrook. Lightly raced mare who is still learning and can improve off that run. TAKETHEMONEYANDRUN (4) returns from a five-month spell. Showed enough in the maiden campaign to suggest he is an each-way chance.
